          "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
          "date": "2013-02-19 03:01:55.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "subject": "LU-2467 pinger: notify client eviction event via MGS",
        "message": "LU-2467 pinger: notify client eviction event via MGS\n\nthis patch makes servers notify eviction event to the clients whose\nexports has been evicted from the servers via MGS.\n\nthe following is one of the routes of this feature.\n\n------------------------\nthe server-side:\n\nclass_fail_export\n  mgc_notify_evict\n    do_fail_export (this was class_fail_export itself before)\n    eviction_notifier_add_req -> to eviction notifier thread\n\n-----------------------\neviction notifier thread: to prepare for lots of clients are\nevicted on lots of targets, this may happen in server's recovery\n\neviction_notifier_main\n  eviction_notifier_handle_reqs\n    ptlrpc_add_req -> to MGS\n\n-----------------------\nMGS:\n\nmgs_handle\n  mgs_notify_evict\n    mgs_notify_evict_to_client\n      ptlrpc_queue_wait -> to clinet\n\n-----------------------\nclient:\nldlm_callback_handler\n  ptlrpc_ping_to_evicted_target\n    ptlrpc_ping -> the target which has evicted the export of\n                   this client\n\nthe client which sent a ping must receive ERROR and will begin\nrecovering.\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: Ib3258747b400646838dda8001376ef7dfacca015\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
